y power and those too weak to seek it.\n\n- J.K. Rowling, Harry Potter and the Sorcerer's Stone\n|\nThere will be moments in your life, when it seems you can no longer go on and you want to give up everything\n\n- Sunday\n|\nHaving to explain to someone how they hurt you, always feels like an ass kicking... again.\n\n- Alfa H, Abandoned Breaths\n|\nTime works so hard for us, if only we can let it.\n\n- Tana French, The Likeness\n|\nA trusting heart will follow, only those who truly follow their heart.\n\n- Anthony\n|\nTo break yourself loose from the dominion, ruler-ship and manipulation of the devil, you have to embrace light (knowledge).\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, The Mountain of Ignorance\n|\nBringing to light what had been hidden in darkness should not overwhelm you, but EDUCATE you.\n\n- Solange\n|\nNever treat your fear as an enemy; it’s a friend in disguise, only if we are able to recognize its worth.\n\n- Mayank S. Sengar, Life and The Grey Notes\n|\nDon't be envious of the Success of others, but let it be your Motivation to thrive\n\n- Samuel\n|\nEquipped with his five senses, man explores the universe around him and calls the adventure Science.\n\n- Edwin\n|\nAll changes, even the most longed for, have their melancholy; for what we leave behind us is a part of ourselves; we must die to one life before we can enter another.\n\n- Anatole\n|\nThe truth is incontrovertible. Malice may attack it, ignorance may deride it, but in the end, there it is.\n\n- Winston\n|\nHolding Eleanor's hand was like holding a butterfly. Or a heartbeat. Like holding something complete, and completely alive.\n\n- Rainbow Rowell, Eleanor & Park\n|\nAnd what’s your unhappiness due to, Harry?The words came out before he had time to think. “Loving someone who loves me.\n\n- Jo Nesbø, The Snowman\n|\nThus I spoke, more and more softly; for I was afraid of my own thoughts and the thoughts behind my thoughts.\n\n- Friedrich\n|\nTo improve a country, educate the citizens.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nRemember, happiness doesn't depend upon who you are or what you have, it depends solely upon what you think.\n\n- Dale\n|\nThe way you walk, way you talk, way you say my name; it's beautiful, wonderful, don't you ever change.\n\n- Taylor Swift, Taylor Swift\n|\nIf life is an adventure, then a vacation is an adventure to find true joy.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nAlways remember that you were once alone, and the crowd you see in your life today are just as unecessary as when you were alone.\n\n- Michael\n|\nDid you ever hear anyone say, 'That work had better be banned because I might read it and it might be very damaging to me'?\n\n- Joseph\n|\nI am a student of life, and don't want to miss any experience. There's poetry in this sort of thing, you know--or perhaps you don't know, but it's all the same.\n\n- H.P. Lovecraft, Old Bugs\n|\nI won't be sad too often,If they bury me in the libraryWith bookworms in my coffin.\n\n- J.\n|\nSome books should be tasted, some devoured, but only a few should be chewed and digested thoroughly.\n\n- Francis\n|\nIf you want to get rich from writing, write the sort of thing that's read by persons who move their lips when they're reading to themselves.\n\n- Don\n|\nFind your gift, the thing you were created for, the thing that inspires you and the thing you are fond of doing, and the thing you are doing better than others\n\n- Sunday\n|\nLOVE is, can, and will.\n\n- Stephanie\n|\nAs the warm air blew in the car, simple snapshots of the life they'd lived together surfaced in his mind; but as always, those images led inexorably to their final day together.\n\n- Nicholas\n|\nThere is an old joke that went around- it goes, in the beginning God made man in His own image, and since the fall, man has been seeking to return the compliment.\n\n- Alistair\n|\nFollow your heart, there lies your happiness.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nUntil we begin to discover and create value, purposefully and systemically, we are not humans but only biomass\n\n- Sunday\n|\nGrief gives you