d itself around her like a tourniquet, keeping her alive even as it condemned a part of her to atrophy.\n\n- Omar El Akkad, American War\n|\nIf you are going to speak out against injustice, if you are angry at ungodliness in the society, then you have the opposing force to contend against.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, The Mountain of Ignorance\n|\nI am right. I`m always right. One time I thought I was wrong, I found out I was right.\n\n- Jerry\n|\n... Now to die of griefwould mean, I'm afraid, to die belatedly, while latecomersare unwelcome, particularly in the future. ...\n\n- Joseph Brodsky, So Forth: Poems\n|\nTo be relevant, you need to be purposeful\n\n- Sunday"